What are microservices:
=======================
-Microservices are an architectural style where an application is built as 
a collection of small,independent and loosely coupled services.

Ex:if we see e-commerce application they might built built different modules for each service like,payment module,user module,order module

why because each module developed independtly and deployed independantly it is very easy debug ,maintain easily and scalable.

How do Microservices diffr with monolithic
==============================================
Architecture:
-------------
In Monolithic application we have single code base that contain all modules tightly coupled with one executable.

In Microservices the decoupled,all the modules are separate entities,each them provide separate business function,the communication happen through api's

Scalability:
-----------
For Monolithic application we will deployed entire project in single server with more cpu specification

But for Microservices each module will deployed in different servers with less cpu it easy to maintain

Deployment
----------
Monolithic application we deployed in single server so if change any small thing we have to re deploy whole application 

But in Microservice we will deploy only that microservice where we want to updates.

