Explain the role of API Gateway in Microservice:
================================================
-An API gateway serves as  a centralized entry point for managing client interactions with microservices.It simplifies communication by routing incoming request to the appropriate microservices and handling various operational responsibilities.

-And  authentication and authorization  the gateway verifies  the user credintials and enforces security policies to ensure that onlt authorized users can access specific services

What is Service Discovery In Microservices:
===========================================
-Service Discovery is mechanism that enables microservices to dynamically locate and communicate with each other within a distributed system.It ensures that service can find and connect to other services without hardcoded configurations ,promoting flexibilty and scalability.

-There are 2 types discoveries

1.Client side discovery
-------------------------

-This particular approach each service is responsible for keep tracking of managing its own service registry.

2.Server side discovery
-------------------------

-Centralized registry such as ureka or a console maintain the locations and the status of all the services.

when client make an request server side the server side load balancer queries the registry and router the request with appropriate service instance.

