--------------
(basically refers to the design of each microservices to be focused around a single well defined resopnsibility or a business capability)

-Autonomous
------------
(Microservice is designed to be autonomous so what does it means they shd operate independently without depending one one another,each microservice should have its own data business logic and the interface so this principle emphasizes loose coupling between the services so that one service failure doesnot effect the other service)

-Business Domain Centric
-------------------------
Microservices shd be aligned with business domains  or capabilities rather than technical layers or function so each service should correspond to a specific business function or a capability making the architecutre more intuitive and closely tied to business objective.

-Resilience
------------
So Basically Microservices  should resilience to failure and designed to gracefully handle disruptions or faults or faults so this includes stratagies like redundency circuit breakers retries and fallback to ensure that a failure in one service doesnot lead a systemwide downtime.

