Automation is a key principle in microservice design and this refers to the use of automated process for deployment ,testing ,scaling and management of microservices so automated pipelines can ensure that microservices can be deployed quickly and reliabily.

How do you ensure Secure in Microservices
========================================
Securing microservice is a crucial thing and it is very important as you need to protect the sensitive data and maintain the integrity of interaction between the services so since microservices typically involve numerous services communicating with one other across different environments so they are more able to various security risks compare to traditional monolithic architecture.so now if you want ensure security in microservice there are few practices that you need to follow.

-Secure Communication
---------------------
Securing Communication refers to encrypting the data exchange between microservices to prevent eavesdropping manin the middle attacks and unauthorized data access so this done by using TLS(Transfort Layer Security) or SSH(Secure Socket Layer)

-Authentication and Authorization
---------------------------------
Authentication and Authorization ensures that only verified and authorized users or Services can access specific resources in the microservices system,authentication verifies the identity of the users of services while authorization defines what actions or resources they can access.

-Service-Level Isolation
-------------------------
Basically this refers to restricting access between microservices to only the necessary communication paths so this ensures that the services interact only with the ones that they are meant to communicate with reducing the risk of attackers and gaining access to other service

